  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2005-07-14",
    "date": "2005-08-02T15:43:56Z",
    "text": "Government Reorganization and Program Performance Improvement Act of 2005 - Authorizes the President to propose establishment in the executive branch of one or more Results Commissions to improve the overall effectiveness, efficiency, or accountability of executive branch operations through reorganization. Requires an Act of Congress for such establishments.\n\nAuthorizes the President to submit to Congress for its consideration a proposed schedule for reviewing the performance of, and need for, executive branch agencies and programs at least once every 10 years. Establishes a Sunset Commission to review them.\n\n\n\nSpecifies procedures for expedited congressional consideration of any reorganization proposal."
  },
